En <a href="http://www.infoworld.com/d/application-development/11-programming-trends-watch-179761">11 programming trends to watch</a>.

Las tendencias:


<ul>
<li>Programming trend No. 1: The JVM is not just for Java anymore</li>
<li>Programming trend No. 2: JavaScript is not just for JavaScript anymore</li>
<li>Programming trend No. 3: No code is an island</li>
<li>Programming trend No. 4: Plantations everywhere</li>
<li>Programming trend No. 5: Openness retreats</li>
<li>Programming trend No. 6: Bandwidth is no longer free</li>
<li>Programming trend No. 7: Energy is no longer free, either</li>
<li>Programming trend No. 8: Traditional education fades from relevance</li>
<li>Programming trend No. 9: Accuracy fades as scalability trumps all</li>
<li>Programming trend No. 10: Real parallelism begins to get practical for all</li>
<li>Programming trend No. 11: GPUs trump CPUs</li>
</ul>

Para pensar un poco.

